body.p: Initial concentration set to 60 pM (in line with insulin secretion).

parameter.name: Km IRS steady state for atp_ratio
Km IRS first phase for datp/dt

body.p: Steady state insulin secretion (IRS) depending on ATP/ADP ratio. Uses a Hill function.

First phase insulin secretion (IRS) depending on the change in ATP: dATP/dt. The rise in ATP concentration triggers closure of APT-sensitive potassium (KATP) channels, which ultimately result in the release of insulin in the bloodstream.
Event for presimulation under given glucose concentration for parameter fitting.
Event added to model to model simulation under given glucose concentration for parameter fitting.
